00:05:59,784 --> 00:06:01,545
Let's take Plants vs. Zombies level one here.

127
00:06:03,065 --> 00:06:05,466
We needed to teach a few basic concepts to the player, like

128
00:06:06,066 --> 00:06:09,807
zombies walk to the left in a straight line and peas shoot to the right in a straight line.

129
00:06:10,613 --> 00:06:11,893
And we could have spelled it out like so,

130
00:06:12,153 --> 00:06:14,474
and put these messages on the screen.

131
00:06:14,854 --> 00:06:17,535
But instead, we wanted to let the player experience it

132
00:06:17,575 --> 00:06:19,696
in a safe environment, like where the player could actually

133
00:06:19,716 --> 00:06:21,176
feel like they're already playing the game.

134
00:06:21,516 --> 00:06:24,657
So what we did was we crafted this really basic level

135
00:06:24,737 --> 00:06:27,258
with just one type of plant, one type of zombie,

136
00:06:27,278 --> 00:06:29,019
the pea shooter, one type of plant, the pea shooter,

137
00:06:29,059 --> 00:06:30,359
one type of zombie, the basic zombie,

138
00:06:30,379 --> 00:06:33,040
and just one single lane where you could plant stuff on.

139
00:06:34,420 --> 00:06:36,841
Here, all the things a player can observe are,

140
00:06:37,121 --> 00:06:39,122
like they can observe that zombies take damage

141
00:06:39,402 --> 00:06:39,862
while they're playing.

142
00:06:40,202 --> 00:06:42,463
They can observe that zombies walk in a straight line.

143
00:06:43,183 --> 00:06:45,203
They can observe that peas shoot in a straight line

144
00:06:45,424 --> 00:06:47,964
and that zombies take about 10 peas to kill.

145
00:06:48,104 --> 00:06:50,745
And they can experience this all within the first level

146
00:06:50,785 --> 00:06:53,846
without us actually putting any words on the screen.

147
00:06:54,326 --> 00:06:55,687
And so the player learns all of this

148
00:06:55,707 --> 00:06:56,667
by simply playing the game.

149
00:06:57,427 --> 00:06:59,248
And we didn't have to explicitly tell them any of it.

150
00:07:01,168 --> 00:07:02,709
Here's another example of where we wanted

151
00:07:02,729 --> 00:07:04,149
to have the player learn by doing.

152
00:07:04,866 --> 00:07:07,447
Hopefully you're all familiar with the shovel in PVZ.

153
00:07:08,168 --> 00:07:10,088
It lets you remove one of your plants

154
00:07:10,469 --> 00:07:11,849
so you can put a new one in its place.

155
00:07:12,650 --> 00:07:15,051
There's a lot of history behind the shovel in PVZ

156
00:07:15,071 --> 00:07:17,852
and how we decided to implement its tutorial.

157
00:07:18,252 --> 00:07:19,653
And I want to go through it all with you

158
00:07:19,753 --> 00:07:22,334
to give you an idea of how much care was placed on letting

159
00:07:22,374 --> 00:07:23,375
the player learn by doing.

